        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You hide insulating crystals or other material that releases a strong static charge when the first creature enters the snare's square. That creature must attempt a @Check[type:reflex|dc:18|traits:uncommon|showDC:all] saving throw.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target takes [[/r {1}[persistent,electricity] #persistent electricity damage]]{1} @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Persistent Damage]{Persistent Electricity Damage}} and takes a -1 circumstance penalty to saving throws against electricity effects for as long as the persistent electricity damage lasts.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, and the target attracts nearby dirt and dust. If the target is or becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Invisible]{Invisible}, it's merely @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Hidden]{Hidden} to creatures that have sight as a precise sense. This effect lasts as long as the persistent electricity damage does.</p>"
